Azure Enterprise Discovery Meeting – Question Bank

1. Business Requirements:

What is driving this cloud migration?
What business problems are you trying to solve?
What are your business objectives?
What are the expected outcomes of this migration?
What defines a successful project?
What are the project timelines and milestones?
Are there any hard deadlines?
Who are the business stakeholders?
Who are the technical stakeholders?
Who will approve architectural decisions?
Are there any future expansion plans?

2. Current Environment Assessment

Can you share the current architecture diagrams?
Can you explain your existing infrastructure?
Is the environment on-premises, cloud, or hybrid?
Which virtualization platform are you using?
Which cloud providers are currently in use?
How many data centers do you have?
How many servers are currently running?
What operating systems are being used?
What databases are currently deployed?
What storage solutions are in use?

3. Application Assessment

How many applications are currently running?
Which applications are business critical?
Which applications require high availability?
Which applications can tolerate downtime?
Which applications are customer-facing?
Which applications are internal?
Which applications are legacy?
Which applications are cloud-ready?
Which applications cannot be migrated?
What technologies are used by the applications?
Are applications tightly coupled?
Are there application dependencies?

4. User and Growth Assessment

How many users currently access the applications?
How many internal users are there?
How many external users are there?
How many users are expected in the next year?
What is the expected growth over the next three to five years?
Are there seasonal traffic spikes?
Are applications accessed globally?
Which regions generate the highest traffic?

5. Networking

Can you explain the current network architecture?
What IP address ranges are currently used?
Are there overlapping IP ranges?
How is connectivity established between locations?
Will Azure require VPN or ExpressRoute connectivity?
Are there existing firewalls?
How is DNS currently managed?
Do you require private connectivity?
Are there existing network segmentation policies?
Are there bandwidth limitations?

6. Identity and Access Management

Which identity provider is currently used?
Is there an on-premises Active Directory?
Is Microsoft Entra ID already implemented?
Are identities synchronized?
Is Multi-Factor Authentication enabled?
Is Conditional Access configured?
Is Privileged Identity Management implemented?
How are administrative accounts managed?
How is Role-Based Access Control managed today?
Are service accounts currently used?

7. Security and Compliance

What security standards must be followed?
Which compliance regulations apply?
Are there internal security policies?
What encryption standards are required?
Are customer-managed keys required?
How are secrets currently managed?
What network security controls exist?
Are vulnerability assessments performed regularly?
Are penetration tests conducted?
Are security audits performed?

8. Governance

Who is allowed to create cloud resources?
Who approves production deployments?
Are naming standards already defined?
Are tagging standards already defined?
Are governance policies currently implemented?
How are subscriptions managed?
Are management groups already in use?
What resource lifecycle policies exist?
How are production changes approved?

9. Monitoring and Operations

Which monitoring tools are currently used?
How are alerts generated?
How are incidents managed?
Is there a centralized operations team?
What are the required Service Level Agreements (SLAs)?
What are the required Service Level Objectives (SLOs)?
How are logs stored?
How long are logs retained?
What operational reports are required?

10. Disaster Recovery and Business Continuity

What Recovery Time Objective (RTO) is required?
What Recovery Point Objective (RPO) is required?
Is cross-region disaster recovery required?
What backup strategy is currently used?
How often are backups performed?
How long are backups retained?
How often is disaster recovery tested?
Which applications require disaster recovery?
What is the acceptable downtime for critical applications?

11. Cost Management

What is the migration budget?
What is the expected monthly cloud budget?
Is there a cost optimization strategy?
Will budgets be assigned to departments?
Is chargeback or showback required?
How are cloud costs monitored?
Are Reserved Instances or Savings Plans planned?
What cost reporting is required?

12. DevOps and Automation

Which source control system is used?
Which CI/CD platform is currently used?
Is Infrastructure as Code mandatory?
Which Infrastructure as Code tool has been selected?
Are automated deployments required?
Are deployment approvals required?
What branching strategy is followed?
Are rollback procedures defined?
How are releases managed?
How are infrastructure changes tracked?
